description: Number of powers x^y (x,y > 1) with n digits.
comments: Conjecture:Lim_n->inf. of a(2n)/10^n=1-1/sqrt(10) andLim_n->inf. of a(2n-1)/10^n=1/sqrt(10)-1/10. _Robert G. Wilson v_, Aug 29 2012
example: a(1) = 3 because there are 3 powers with 1 digit: 2^2, 2^3 and 3^2.
author: Michel ten Voorde (seqfan(AT)tenvoorde.org) Apr 10 2001
